Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: The Holy Family resting in front of a cave on the flight into Egypt. Mountainous landscape with Joseph reclining at centre next to the grazing ass, the Virgin attended to by two angels as she sits with the Christ Child at right; proof before letters; from a series of four plates Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment see 1844,0425.15. This is first state, for impressions of the second state of this plate, see S.2278 and F,2.207.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (9.I)
Acquisition notes: For the history of the acquisition of the Sheepshanks collection, please see Sheepshanks.1
